            "body": "> You should be able to use a single :undo to revert the changes from nvim_buf_set_lines(), however if the buffer was unloaded then the undo information gets mangled\r\n\r\nThat might be expected, `set nohidden` destroys undo info if the buffer is hidden (unloaded). That is, unloading a buffer loses its in-memory undo info, by design.",
